0.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have i guess newb questions</span><hr size=1> Alright, now I feel really bad for not being able to SoW you when you asked. -lol-<br>
<br>
As a high elf Enchantress I solo'd until level 16 because I could never get a group before that. Until I got level 16 I pretty much stayed in the faydark continent. If you are level 10 now you can probably go to steamfont hills and kill the skeletons there or even some elementals and other things. You will of course need to be really careful because things can get out of hand pretty fast when they start to run away.<br>
<br>
At level 16 you can go to Lake of ill omen (you will want to go to FV anyways to get your first mana regen spell &quot;breeze&quot;) and fight at the mill area. I would suggest grouping also as an enchanting class. My experiences have found grouping in dungeons to be far more enjoyable for myself than grouping outside or solo'ing. =)<br>
<br>
Another thing that may help you with your money problems are to sell enchanted bars of silver. (I think you get enchant silver at level <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You can buy the silver bar for under 6 gold and then sell for 7 to 10 gold each after you enchant it. This will take time of course as the spell is 60 mana a shot and at level 10 you don't have all that much mana, but it is an option.<br>
<br>
As far as your being bound in Gfaydark and fighting in the commons area, I would suggest to get rebound in freeport so that when you die, (Yes we all die sooner or later) you won't have a huge distance and a boat ride to get back to your body.<br>
<br>
I also would advise against killing the sisters in ocean of tears because of the faction problem. If you are a high elf which it would look that you are because of fighting on orc hill and CB entrance you will have a heck of a time getting back to your guild to train and such when you are back in the high elf city. =)<br>
<br>
I really hope this helps some, and I hope that you also can understand how frustrating it can be to get a random tell from someone you don't know who is anon asking for a spell you can't even cast. More so when you have found someone doing something bad and they don't like the fact that you know.<br>
<br>
Lyena/Lara<br>
<br>
